author: Russell Brand
description:
A French court just ruled it's not defamatory to say Brigitte Macron is a man—and the internet has exploded. Piers Morgan, Candace Owens, and a chorus of critics are weighing in. But beyond the genital jokes and bizarre theories, is there something deeper here? What does it mean when world leaders have secrets they’d rather not discuss—sexual or otherwise?
